<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870401-0094 </DOCNO><HL> Safety-Kleen Corp. BuysA McKesson Corp. Unit</HL><DD> 04/01/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SK MCKTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> SAN FRANCISCO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   McKesson Corp. said it sold its McKesson Envirosystems Co. unit to Safety-Kleen Corp.    Terms weren't disclosed. The unit is a solvent-refining company with plants in Kentucky, Illinois and Puerto Rico. The sale to Elgin, Ill.-based Safety-Kleen, which makes parts cleaners and offers related solvent recycling services, continues McKesson's divestiture of businesses not part of its core operations.    In November, McKesson sold its chemical distribution company, and in December sold its environmental resources business.    McKesson distributes pharmaceutical, health and beauty products, household goods and other items. </TEXT></DOC>